  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Purpose: Hip fracture is a common disease on elderly. They become disabled easily if no
      adequate rehabilitation was given. The aim of the study is to compare the effectiveness of
      different types of post acute rehabilitation care for hip fracture.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Method: This study will recruit 150 peoples with hip fracture from hospitals in Taipei from
      Jan 1, 2014 to Dec 31, 2014. The subjects from wards are randomly divided into group A, B
      and Group C. Each group includes 50 cases of hip fracture. Group C received 14 days
      hospitalization for comprehensive rehabilitation and 6 times home rehabilitation services
      within 3 months; Group B received 14 days hospitalization for comprehensive rehabilitation
      and Group A was control group.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
